text: Pajala IF is a sports club club in Pajala in Sweden. It was established in 1930. It originally played soccer. It later also adopted basketball, table tennis, soccer, floorball, ice hockey, skiing and volleyball. The men's volleyball team played in the Swedish top division during the season of 2000-2001. == References == ==Other websites== * Official website Category:1930 establishments in Sweden Category:Basketball clubs in Sweden Category:Floorball clubs in Sweden Category:Ice hockey teams in Sweden Category:Ski clubs in Sweden Category:Swedish football clubs Category:Table tennis clubs in Sweden Category:Volleyball clubs in Sweden
